Zoogeographic and bathymetric distribution. The species has a widespread distribution at tropical and subtropical latitudes in the Atlantic (
Fig. 6
). Within this latitudinal range it has been quite consistently collected whenever sampling for mesoplankton has been carried out at depths> 3000 m . However, there has not been enough deep sampling at latitudes> 30 ° to state categorically that its range is restricted to low latitudes. Nor can it be considered to be endemic to the Atlantic, although presently its known range does appear restricted to the Atlantic. However, its distribution does appear to be related to North Atlantic Deep Water, if so, then it may well be dispersed within this water mass into other oceans.
